# UAT docker-compose — generated by backend/services/uat_provisioner.py (v0.9.0 Phase 2, CR-1).
#
# Generalized: passes through ALL source-project services (db/backend/frontend, plus qdrant,
# redis, workers, …) preserving their image/build, environment, volumes, healthchecks,
# extra_hosts (e.g. Ollama host.docker.internal:host-gateway) and networks (incl. external nets).
#
# Routing is via Traefik (Phase-1 infra), NOT host ports: the frontend + backend services join the
# external `nex-proxy-net` and carry the exact Traefik labels from the live ledger migration
# (frontend = Host catch-all @ priority 10; backend = Host && PathPrefix(/api) @ priority 20).
#
# The top-level `name: uat-<slug>` namespaces every unnamed network/volume with that project
# prefix so the UAT cannot clobber the source project's running containers/volumes.
#
# Backend env vars (incl. SYNTHETIC secrets) are read from the sibling `.env` (chmod 600,
# gitignored, NEVER committed) — there is no hardcoded credential in this file.
#
# The networks/services/volumes below are emitted by the provisioner via the `to_yaml` filter
# (robust block-style dump of the arbitrary N-service structure).
name: {{ COMPOSE_NAME }}

{{ COMPOSE_BODY | to_yaml }}
